{"article_id":"MG8GKC63y9ugcmam","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The big drop in the unemployment rate a month before the presidential election brought cries of disbelief and conspiracy theories from Jack Welch and other critics of the Obama administration Friday .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"But the Labor Department was quick to dismiss such claims .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"`` Unbelievable jobs numbers ..","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"these Chicago guys will do anything ..","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"ca n't debate","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"so change numbers , ''","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"tweeted Welch , the former CEO of General Electric","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"( GE ) .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"Obama 's economy","depth":2},{"id":9,"text":"View photos","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"A look at where the economy stood","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"when Obama took office","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"and what 's changed since .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Welch did not respond to a request for further comment .","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"In an interview later in the day on MSNBC , he admitted","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"that he had no evidence","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"that the jobs numbers were manipulated ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"but said","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"they `` defy logic . '' The unemployment rate fell to 7.8 % in September , down from 8.1 % a month earlier .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"The drop was due to the Bureau of Labor Statistics ' survey of households","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"showing","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"that 873,000 more people had jobs than in the previous month .","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"That was the biggest one-month gain in more than nine years .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"`` This is a methodology","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"that 's been used for decades .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"And it is insulting","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"when you hear people just cavalierly say","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"that somehow we 're manipulating numbers , ''","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Solis told CNN 's Richard Quest .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"Welch was n't alone in raising questions about the jobs numbers .","depth":4},{"id":30,"text":"Americans for Limited Government , a conservative group","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"that has been a steady critic of the Obama administration ,","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"issued a statement","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"that said","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"the numbers","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"the BLS `` used","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"to calculate the unemployment rate","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"are wrong , or worse manipulated .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Given that these numbers conveniently meet Obama 's campaign promises one month before the election ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"the conclusions are obvious .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"Anyone","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"who takes this unemployment report serious","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"is either naive","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"or a paid Obama campaign adviser . ''","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Conn Carroll , a senior writer at the conservative Washington Examiner suggested a slightly less nefarious form of manipulation of the data .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"BLS cooked numbers .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"I think","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"a bunch of Dems lied","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"about getting jobs .","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"That would have same effect , ''","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"he tweeted .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"`` Would love to see the partisan breakdown of the 873,000 Americans","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"who say","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"they got new jobs . ''","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"BLS denied","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"there was any manipulation of the data or anything out of the ordinary about the unemployment rate calculation .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"`` No political appointee is involved in the collecting , processing and analyzing of the data , ''","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"said Thomas Nardone , the associate commissioner for employment and unemployment statistics .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Nardone said","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"the Council of Economic Advisers does n't get the numbers until Thursday afternoon ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"and that the Secretary of Labor he rself does n't see them until Friday morning .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"Even some conservative economists defended the BLS 's integrity and legitimacy of the numbers .","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"`` The jobs # 's may look fishy to some ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"but","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"if you step back ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"it 's just a plow horse economy","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"lumbering along , ''","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"tweeted Brian Wesbury , chief economist at First Trust .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":137,"left":76,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":76,"left":0,"right":75,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":75,"left":1,"right":74,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":74,"left":72,"right":73,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":72,"left":2,"right":71,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":71,"left":3,"right":70,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":70,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":73,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":8,"right":135,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":135,"left":95,"right":134,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":79,"right":94,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":79,"left":9,"right":78,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":78,"left":77,"right":12,"relation":"joint","nuclea